<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="97" start="start">Tree</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
: columnar to spreading, height to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
, evergreen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Bark</emphasis>
: dark brown, friable, fissured horizontally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Roots</emphasis>
: both stilt roots and aerial roots growing from lower branches, stilt roots are highly conspicuous arching above ground to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Leaves</emphasis>
: simple, opposite, green to dark green, elliptical to broadly elliptical (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2D, E</figureCitation>
), laterally folded, underside with numerous dark spots, 7-13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="4.0" unit="cm" value="6.25" valueMax="8.5" valueMin="4.0">4-8.5 cm</quantity>
, length to width ratio averaging 1.69 (not greater than 1.8), apex obtuse with pointed mucro, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" unit="cm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.4-0.5 cm</quantity>
long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2F</figureCitation>
), base cuneate, margin entire; petiole green, 1.5-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3-0.5 cm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Inflorescences</emphasis>
: axillary, 2-6 flowered (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2G</figureCitation>
); bract and bracteoles minute (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2H</figureCitation>
); peduncle 2-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" unit="cm" value="0.4" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.3">0.3-0.5 cm</quantity>
; pedicel stout; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Mature flower</emphasis>
: ellipsoidal, creamy white (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2I</figureCitation>
), 1.4-1.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7.0" unit="cm" value="0.8" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.7">0.7-0.9 cm</quantity>
, length to width ratio 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">ca.</emphasis>
1.87, cross section slightly four-sided (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2J</figureCitation>
); calyx lobes 4, thicker than 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizophora mucronata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Rhizophora mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, yellowish white, apex acute; petals 4, thick, leathery, folded laterally, creamy white, velvety and hairy on the margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2L, N</figureCitation>
), 0.9-1.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" unit="cm" value="0.35" valueMax="0.4" valueMin="0.3">0.3-0.4 cm</quantity>
; stamens 4, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" unit="cm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.5-0.7cm</quantity>
long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2M, N</figureCitation>
); style bilobed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2O</figureCitation>
), 0.8-
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" unit="cm" value="0.12">0.12 cm</quantity>
long, seated on four sided domed ovary (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii (A) habit (B) stem base with stilt roots (C) bark (D) branches (E) leafy branch end with flowers (F) leaf apex with mucro (G) inflorescence (H) minute bract at dichotomous inflorescence branch (I) mature bud with minute bracteole below calyx (J) cross section of bud (K) mature propagules (L) thick leathery petal (M) stamens (N) flower (O) pistil showing four-sided ovary (P) flower with one petal removed (Q) pear-shaped fruit (R) stamens with pollen." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.52.5037.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/46979" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">2P</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Mature fruits</emphasis>
: pear-shaped, brown, 4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.5" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.5">2.5-3.5 cm</quantity>
, calyx persistent with erect lobes (Fig. 
