</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="97" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="97">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="97">
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. Ragavan" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizophora mucronata subsp. var. var. alokii" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mucronata" subSpecies="var." variety="alokii">Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from Austin Creek, North Andaman, India.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="habitat and ecology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="98" start="start">Habitat</pageBreakToken>
and ecology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
It grows in a mangrove forest along the banks in an intermediate estuarine position in association with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizophora apiculata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apiculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Rhizophora apiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizophora mucronata" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mucronata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Rhizophora mucronata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. B. Robinson" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Perr." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Ceriops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceriops tagal" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tagal">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Ceriops tagal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Flowering December to March; fruiting April to July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Named in honour of Dr. Alok Saxena (Principal Chief Conservator of Forests) for his inspiration and his outstanding contribution to mangrove conservation in the ANI.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. Ragavan" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizophora mucronata subsp. var. var. alokii" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="98" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mucronata" subSpecies="var." variety="alokii">Rhizophora mucronata var. alokii</taxonomicName>
was collected only from Austin Creek (North Andaman Islands). At this site ca. 15 individuals were observed and hence it is assumed to be rare. At present, until further areas can be sampled the species can be accessed as &quot;Data Deficient&quot; (DD), using the criteria of 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom" pageId="5" pageNumber="100" refId="B6" refString="IUCN, 2001. IUCN Red List categories and criteria. Version 3.1, Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland, and Cambridge, United Kingdom" title="IUCN Red List categories and criteria. Version 3.1, Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission." year="2001">IUCN (2001)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
